$ ctria3_axial_force.bdf
$ Two CTRIA3 forming a 1 m × 1 m square — axial extension
$
$ Geometry: same square as CQUAD4 test, split along diagonal 1-3
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, t = 0.1 m
$ Load:     1000 N total in +x (500 N at nodes 2 and 3)
$ BCs:      fix T1 of nodes 1 and 4 (left edge), fix T2 of node 1
$           fix T3 of nodes 1, 2, 4 (out-of-plane stability — non-collinear)
$
$ Hand calculation:
$   A = 1 * 0.1 = 0.1 m²
$   δ = F*L / (E*A) = 0.01 m  (CST represents linear field exactly)
$   σ_x = 10000 Pa in both elements
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTRIA3 AXIAL FORCE
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: corners of 1x1 plate in the xy-plane
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
$ Material
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3
$ Shell property: t = 0.1 m
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
$ Two CTRIA3 elements (CCW node order viewed from +z)
CTRIA3,1,1,1,2,3
CTRIA3,2,1,1,3,4
$ In-plane BCs: fix T1 of left-edge nodes; fix T2 of node 1
SPC1,1,1,1
SPC1,1,1,4
SPC1,1,2,1
$ Out-of-plane: fix T3, R1, R2 (DOFs 3,4,5) of all nodes.
$ For a flat plate with purely in-plane loading, no out-of-plane response exists.
$ Constraining these DOFs eliminates bending singularity cleanly.
SPC1,1,345,1
SPC1,1,345,2
SPC1,1,345,3
SPC1,1,345,4
$ Loads: 500 N in +x at each right-edge node
FORCE,1,2,0,500.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
FORCE,1,3,0,500.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
ENDDATA
